By Bashir Yahuza Malumfashi Arise and hail  The great Nigerian  Nationalist of vision Bukar of mission  Yamtarawala of our time.  Arise and glorify  Allah the Glorious  Universe He controls  Yamtarawala He guides.  Arise and salute,  Muhammad the guider,  Generosity, a pillar  To Khadijas, a master,  Yamtarawala greets.  Arise oh my people,  Attention and listen  Be ready we visit  Yamtarawala of great.  Arise and be aware,  When thunder claps,  The signs are vivid, clear  Ponder —decipher.  Arise and learn,  The day he’s come  10th number is great  12th is even bright.  1942 of gold, prime.  Arise, let’s tour,  King’s College of honour,  Usman’s son tested the gruel.  Arise and be focused  ABU is more than a name,  PhD is not a joke,  Yamta —gallant, brave.  Arise, come and hear,  The short of courage,  Bravery, candour Yamta the legend,  Biu is free and famed.  Arise for the man  The last as he stands  Bukar Namiji adored  Man with pen armed  Yamtarawala of light.  Arise, come in haste  Behold the elephant grass,  Knows no drought,  Knight in fitted armour.  Arise, stand still  For a true nationalist,  Tireless, cleaner record Vanguard of all time.  Arise, thumbs up  For Shakespeare is back  With overflowing ink,  Scoring brighter scores.  Arise and honour,  Double edged pen.  Hausa, English, double journey  Ajami —triple sojourn. Arise for the master,  Doyen, man of letters,  Literary guru striking,  Pen gripped nay sword Saving, shielding, enlightening.  Arise, come and count,  Hatching Hopes, a biography Folktales, a compendium,  In Biu, there is history  Yesterday, today and all time.  Culled from Songs for Bukar Usman